milestones.description: Ian Chappell has become the top scorer in ODIs with 316 runs, going past Dennis Amiss's 302
Ian Chappell's 86 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for AUS), surpassing Ian Chappell's 83
Ken Wadsworth's 104 is the highest individual score in ODIs (for NZ), surpassing Bevan Congdon's 82
Ken Wadsworth has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (64) in an innings in ODIs for NZ, going past Bevan Congdon's 40
Ian Chappell has scored 4 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, the most for AUS breaking Stackpole's record
Ken Wadsworth has become the top scorer for NZ in ODIs with 144 runs, going past Bevan Congdon's 87
Ken Wadsworth has broken the record for most runs in boundaries (64) in an innings in ODIs, going past Dennis Amiss's 62
Mallett has become the top wicket-taker for AUS in ODIs with 8 wickets, going past Greg Chappell's 5
Dayle Hadlee has become the top wicket-taker for NZ in ODIs with 6 wickets, going past Bevan Congdon's 5
This is the highest match aggregate (499) involving teams Australia & New Zealand in ODIs
Bevan Congdon has conceded the most runs in an innings (77) in ODIs for NZ, going past Collinge's record of 52
Australia's 265 is the highest total in ODIs, surpassing Australia's 240
Ian Chappell has scored 4 fifty-plus scores in ODIs, breaking Stackpole's record
Bevan Congdon has conceded the most runs in an innings (77) in ODIs, going past David Colley's record of 72
Greg Chappell has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (6) for AUS, going past Ian Chappell
Mark Burgess has broken the record for playing the most ODIs (5) for NZ, going past Bevan Congdon
Bevan Congdon and Ken Wadsworth's 130-run partnership is NZ's highest for any wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 55 between Glenn Turner and Vic Pollard
Ian Chappell and Greg Chappell's 74-run partnership is the highest for the 3rd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 66 between Ian Chappell and Doug Walters
Bevan Congdon and Ken Wadsworth's 130-run partnership is the highest for the 6th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 45 between Mark Burgess and Ken Wadsworth
Ian Chappell and Greg Chappell's 74-run partnership is AUS's highest for the 3rd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 66 between Ian Chappell and Doug Walters
Ian Redpath and Greg Chappell's 29-run partnership is AUS's highest for the 5th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 24 between Doug Walters and Stackpole
John Parker and Peter Coman's 39-run partnership is NZ's highest for the 2nd wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 12 between Bevan Congdon and Glenn Turner
Bevan Congdon and Ken Wadsworth's 130-run partnership is NZ's highest for the 6th wicket in ODIs, breaking the record of 45 between Mark Burgess and Ken Wadsworth
